text: Agdistis protecta is a moth in the family Pterophoridae. It is known from Turkmenistan and Iran.A new species, a new synonym, and new distribution records in the genus Agdistis Hübner, 1825 from Iran (Pterophoridae: Agdistinae) The wingspan is 15–17 mm.Pterophoridae aus Zentralasien und angrenzenden Territorien.- 2.
